(78, 10, '_solution', '<p>One essential component of successful events is to import and follow up with your event attendees immediately after the event and answer their questions. By doing so, you show them that you care about their questions and nurture the relationship. These activities help NextData get better responses when your team members follow up with these potential prospects.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5>Step-by-step Guide</h5>\r\n\r\n<p><p><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">1</span> In today\'s challenge, you will learn the essential platform capabilities that you will use in your day-to-day job. To start, you need to import the attendee list into Account Engagement. Before importing the list, there are some preparations that you need to make. Always review the file you are going to import and ensure that there are no missing headers, generic emails, or missing rows.</p> \r\n\r\n<p>You can use the dataset from the resource section for this task. Once you are satisfied with the file, follow the steps below to import the attendee list. For the event follow-up task, you will import event attendees to a static list.</p>\r\n\r\n[guide id=\"37\" status=\"closed\"]\r\n\r\n<p class=\"pt-3\"><p><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">2</span> Next, before creating a new list email, you need to import the email template. You can find the email template in the resource section or use an existing template. If you haven\'t imported an email template before, I encourage you to practice it. Email Templates are commonly used in Account Engagement, so it\'s important to know how to work with them.</p>\r\n\r\n[guide id=\"59\" status=\"closed\"]\r\n\r\n<p class=\"pt-3\"><p><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">3</span> So far, you have imported the attendee list and the email template. The final step is to combine everything and send an email. For adhoc email sends, you can utilize the List Emails feature. It allows you to easily select your template, add your own content, and schedule the email. List Email is convenient for sending emails quickly.</p>\r\n\r\n[guide id=\"78\" status=\"open\"]'),
(79, 10, '__solution', 'field_64dd1a2d9923a'),
(80, 12, '_description', '<p class=\"mb-0\">At NextData, your recent trade show event was a great success. Many prospects visited your booth and expressed interest in seeing a product demo. Your team now wants to send a follow-up email to these prospects. Your task is to segment the event list, identify the prospects who indicated interest in the demo, and schedule a follow-up email.</p>'),
(81, 12, '__description', 'field_64dd19ca99237'),
(82, 12, '_resources', '<p>On Day 1, you imported the event attendee list, but the team forgot to include the information about the prospects who requested to see the demo. A new file has been sent, which includes a new \"product_demo_interest\" column. If the value in this column is \"Yes,\" it indicates that the prospect would like to see a demo. Below, you will find the email template and the copy for the follow-up email.</p>\r\n\r\n<!-- Table start -->\r\n<h3 class=\"fs-5 my-4 text-success\">Dataset</h3>\r\n<table class=\"table table-striped\">\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th scope=\"col\">email</th>\r\n<th scope=\"col\">product_demo_interest</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>mlawther0@sciencedirect.com</td>\r\n<td>Yes</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>phutcheon1@telegraph.co.uk</td>\r\n<td>No</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>cpossell2@github.io</td>\r\n<td>Yes</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>gdirkin3@latimes.com</td>\r\n<td>Yes</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>zdaveren4@eventbrite.com</td>\r\n<td>Yes</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<!-- Table end -->\r\n\r\n<!-- Button start -->\r\n<a href=\"https://github.com/sabuhiy/mc30/blob/main/ae30-03-event-attendees.csv\" class=\"btn btn-success rounded-pill text-white\" target=\"_blank\">üíæ Download .csv</a>\r\n<!-- Button end -->\r\n\r\n<!-- Template start -->\r\n<h3 class=\"fs-5 my-4 text-success\">Templates</h3>\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n	<div class=\"col-md-5\">\r\n		<a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/em_event_followup.png\">\r\n			<img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/em_event_followup.png\" class=\"img-fluid border rounded-1 p-1 mx-auto\">\r\n		</a>	\r\n		\r\n		<div class=\"d-grid mt-3\"><a href=\"https://github.com/sabuhiy/account-engagement-email-templates/blob/main/ae30-03-em-event-followup.html\" class=\"btn btn-success rounded-pill text-white\" target=\"_blank\">‚¨áÔ∏è Email Template</a></div>\r\n		<div class=\"d-grid mt-3\"><a href=\"https://www.nextinc.xyz/ae30-03-em-event-followup\" class=\"btn btn-outline-primary rounded-pill\"  target=\"_blank\">üîç Email Preview</a></div>	\r\n	</div>                   \r\n</div>\r\n<!-- Template end -->'),
