(86, 12, '_solution', '<p>Timely post-event follow-ups are important, especially if you had prospects who requested a demo. It is also crucial to provide them with an easy way to schedule a demo at their convenience. Today, you will use Account Engagement\'s Dynamic Lists and Email Send capabilities to accomplish this task.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5>Step-by-step Guide</h5>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">1</span> As you have seen on the new list, there is a new column where prospects indicated their interest in seeing a product demo by selecting \"yes\" or \"no\". To import this data into Account Engagement, you need to create a custom field. Follow the guide below to create a new custom field named \"Product Demo Interest\".</p>\r\n\r\n[guide id=\"114\" status=\"open\"]\r\n\r\n<p class=\"pt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">2</span> Once you have created the new field, you can proceed to the next step of importing the new list. Repeat the steps you followed on Day 1. Ensure that the product_demo_interest column from the CSV file is correctly mapped to the corresponding field in Account Engagement.</p>\r\n\r\n[guide id=\"37\" status=\"closed\"]\r\n\r\n<p class=\"pt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">3</span> Next, you will create a dynamic list that includes all trade show attendees who expressed interest in seeing the product demo. You can use the criteria where the prospect\'s custom field \"Product Demo Interest\" is set to \"yes\".</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/ae30-03-dl-product-demo-interest-1.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/ae30-03-dl-product-demo-interest-1.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\r\n\r\n[guide id=\"120\" status=\"closed\"] \r\n\r\n<p class=\"pt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">4</span> The final step is to create a new list email using the template provided in the resources section. You can also use the template that you imported on Day 1. Modify the content of the email as needed. A sample email copy is also available for reference. Once you are satisfied with the email, proceed to the next tab and select the recipient list you created in the previous step. Once the email has been thoroughly tested, it is ready to be sent.</p>\r\n\r\n[guide id=\"78\" status=\"closed\"] \r\n'),
