(94, 11, '_solution', '<p>A landing page is a crucial component of your event campaign as it helps attract prospects who are interested in attending your event. You can customize your forms to gather additional information about potential prospects (we will cover this in future challenges). Any information collected through these forms will greatly assist you in measuring the success of their campaigns.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5>Step-by-step Guide</h5>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">1</span> First, we need to create a layout template which determines how your landing page functions and looks. To create an initial layout template, you need to copy and paste the HTML code from the link in the resources section into Account Engagement. Follow the steps below to import your first layout template.</p>\r\n\r\n[guide id=\"93\" status=\"closed\"]\r\n\r\n<p class=\"pt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">2</span> Next, you need to create a form. To control the visual appearance of your forms, you should use a layout template. You can utilize the layout template you have just created. Proceed by creating a new form that will have email, first name, last name, and company fields.</p>\r\n\r\n[guide id=\"95\" status=\"closed\"]\r\n\r\n<p class=\"pt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">3</span> In the last step, you will build a landing page using the layout template and form. Follow the steps below to create your first landing page. As you set it up, you will be asked to choose a layout template and a form. Use the assets you created in Step 1 and Step 2, respectively. Once you are happy with the overall look of the landing page, publish it and share the link with your marketing team.</p>\r\n\r\n[guide id=\"108\" status=\"open\"]'),
