(259, 126, '_description', '<p class=\"mb-0\">The marketing team at NextData wants to find a way to notify sales team members when one of their prospects registers for the upcoming product launch event. They are also wondering if it is possible to tag those registered prospects. Your task today is to use completion actions to ensure that record owners are notified whenever a prospect fills out the event form, and to tag those prospects as \'2023_product_launch\'.</p>'),
(260, 126, '__description', 'field_64dd19ca99237'),
(261, 126, '_detail', 'For today\'s challenge, you will explore completion action types and learn how to leverage one of these types to notify the contact owner and tag prospects who fill out the product event form. This challenge is a great opportunity to understand how you can effectively categorize prospects by leveraging these capabilities.'),
(262, 126, '__detail', 'field_64e26bc8efb7b'),
(263, 126, '_resources', '<p>You will use the same landing page and form from Day 2. If you missed creating it, you can use the provided template below for your landing page and preview it <a href=\"https://www.nextinc.xyz/ae30-02-lp-nextdata-event-promotion\" class=\"text-primary\">here</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"fs-5 my-4 text-success\">Templates</h3>\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n	<div class=\"col-md-5\">\r\n		<a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/page-event-promotion.png\">\r\n		<img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/page-event-promotion.png\" class=\"img-fluid border rounded-1 p-1\">\r\n		</a>\r\n		<div class=\"d-grid mt-3\"><a href=\"https://github.com/sabuhiy/account-engagement-layout-templates/blob/main/AE30-02-LT-Event-Promotion.html\" class=\"btn btn-success rounded-pill text-white\" target=\"_blank\">‚¨áÔ∏è Layout Template</a></div>\r\n		<div class=\"d-grid mt-3\"><a href=\"https://www.nextinc.xyz/ae30-02-lp-nextdata-event-promotion\" class=\"btn btn-outline-primary rounded-pill\" target=\"_blank\">üîç Landing Page Preview</a></div>		\r\n	</div>                   \r\n</div>'),
