(266, 126, '__links', 'field_64dd1a2199239'),
(267, 126, '_solution', '<p>Account Engagement\'s completion actions on forms can help streamline your internal processes. By setting up notifications and tags, you can keep your team updated and categorize prospects effectively.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5>Step-by-step Guide</h5>\r\n\r\n<p>For this task, you need to add two completion actions to the existing product launch event form: <strong>Notify assigned user</strong> and <strong>Add tags</strong>. The order in which you trigger these completion actions does not matter for this task, so you can start with either one.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">1</span> To set up completion actions, go to the Completion Actions tab on the form and scroll down to the Completion Actions section. To notify the record owner every time a prospect submits the form, select <strong>Notify assigned user</strong> from the Action dropdown. </p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/ae30-04-completion-action-02.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/ae30-04-completion-action-02.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"pt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">2</span> To tag prospects, select <strong>Add tags</strong> from the Action dropdown and enter <code>2023_product_launch</code> for prospects who fill out the form.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/ae30-04-completion-action-03.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/ae30-04-completion-action-03.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\r\n\r\n[guide id=\"121\" status=\"closed\"]\r\n'),
