(290, 127, '_solution', '<p>Account Management is a robust platform to use for your event management initiatives. The platform offers built-in capabilities to track event registrations and create automated emails for pre and post-event engagement.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5>Step-by-step Guide</h5>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">1</span> For today\'s challenge, you need to create a list to capture all registrants for the product launch event. There are multiple ways to achieve this. One straightforward approach is to create a dynamic list that automatically updates whenever a new prospect signs up for the event. In the dynamic list criteria, select the <strong>Prospect landing page</strong> and choose the name of the landing page. Then, select <strong>was successfully completed</strong>. Alternatively, if the form is embedded on an external website, use the <strong>Prospect form</strong> criteria and select the name of the form. Then, select <strong>was successfully completed</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/day-5-dynamic-list-new.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/day-5-dynamic-list-new.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\r\n\r\n[guide id=\"120\" status=\"closed\"]\r\n\r\n<p class=\"mt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">2</span> Next, to create an autoresponder, you need to create a new email template. When creating a new email template, go to the <strong>Available</strong> for section and check the <strong>Autoresponder emails</strong> option. This will make the template available for the <strong>Send an autoresponder email</strong> action.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/day-5-autoresponder-new.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/day-5-autoresponder-new.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\r\n\r\n[guide id=\"59\" status=\"closed\"]\r\n\r\n<p class=\"mt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">3</span> The final step is to add a new action to the product launch event form. Go to the <strong>Completion Actions</strong> tab on the form and select <strong>Send an auto responder email</strong> under <strong>Actions</strong>. Then, enter the name of the recently created email template and select it.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/day-5-select-autoresponder-new.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/day-5-select-autoresponder-new.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>'),
