(617, 366, '_solution', '<p>Custom redirects are a fundamental feature in Account Engagement, enabling a variety of functions such as capturing registrant details for events. In this guide, you\'ll learn to create a flow that allows registrants to confirm their attendance through custom redirects.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5>Step-by-step Guide</h5>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">1</span> The initial step involves setting up a landing page to act as a confirmation page, showcasing event details. Utilize the layout template available in the resource section. Follow this guide to publish your landing page:</p>\r\n\r\n[guide id=\"108\" status=\"closed\"]\r\n\r\n<p class=\"mt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">2</span> Next, create a static list to gather registrants from the custom redirects. This list will be used in the completion action for the custom redirect. Here\'s how you can create a static list:</p>\r\n\r\n[guide id=\"371\" status=\"closed\"]\r\n\r\n<p class=\"mt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">3</span> After setting up the landing page and static list, it\'s time to create your custom redirect. Ensure the Destination URL field points to the landing page URL from Step 1. Choose <strong>Add to list</strong> under Completion Actions, linking to the list created in Step 2.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/ae30-08-cr-event-confirmation.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/ae30-08-cr-event-confirmation.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\r\n\r\n[guide id=\"375\" status=\"closed\"]\r\n\r\n<p class=\"mt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">4</span> Finally, integrate the custom redirect link into your email communication. This completes the process, enabling a seamless flow in Account Engagement for event attendance confirmation.</p>'),
