(695, 386, '_solution', '<p>Using Dynamic Content in Account Engagement opens up endless possibilities for what you can do. Today\'s task was a simple use case: showing a personalized message when a senior executive submits the form. By leveraging dynamic content, you are able to provide a unique experience to prospect in different roles.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5>Step-by-step Guide</h5>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">1</span> For today\'s challenge, the first task is to create dynamic content. Your goal is to identify senior executives and display a custom message specifically tailored for them. To do this, you will use the <strong>Job Title</strong> field as criteria to show different variations of the content.</p>\r\n<p>To begin, navigate to the Variations section and click on the <strong>Add Variation</strong> button. Enter the criteria as follows: the Job Title contains Chief, CTO, CEO, CIO, or VP of. Then, add a custom message that will be displayed if the Job Title matches any of these values.</p>\r\n<p>Once saved, you can proceed to use this dynamic content on the landing page form in the next step.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/day-10-dynamic-content.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/day-10-dynamic-content.png\" alt=\"Dynamic Content Creation\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"mt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">2</span> Before adding dynamic content to the confirmation page, you need to modify the form by including a new Job Title field. To do this, go to the Fields tab on the form and add a new field. After adding the field, navigate to the Completion Actions tab and add the dynamic content to the <strong>Thank You Content</strong> window.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/day-10-update-form.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/day-10-update-form.png\" alt=\"Form Update\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"mt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">3</span> After updating the form, go to the landing page and test the form by entering different job titles. For example, if you enter \"CEO\" as the job title, the custom messages should be displayed.</p>\r\n'),
