(810, 409, '_solution', '<p>Account Engagement offers a wide range of capabilities that enable marketers to easily create complex automations. One of these capabilities is Automation Rules, which can efficiently handle multiple tasks. In today‚Äôs challenge, you will learn how to use an Automation Rule to update the prospect score. This is just the beginning, as you will explore more about Automation Rules in the upcoming challenges.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5>Step-by-step Guide</h5>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">1</span> Today\'s challenge involves creating a new landing page for the demo request page and including a form within it. You can utilize the templates provided in the resources section on the left.</p>\r\n\r\n[guide id=\"95\" status=\"closed\"]\r\n\r\n[guide id=\"108\" status=\"closed\"]\r\n\r\n<p class=\"mt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">2</span> Next, to capture the prospect\'s Job Level, create a new custom field in Account Engagement. Name the field <strong>Job Level</strong> and set the field type as <strong>Dropdown</strong>. The dropdown field should include the following values: C-Suite, Vice President, Director, Manager, Other.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-13-new-field.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-13-new-field.png\" alt=\"New Custom Field Creation\" class=\"img-fluid\"></a></div>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"mt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">3</span> After creating the new field, update the form by adding the Job Level field to it. When adding a field to a form, select <strong>Load Default Data</strong> to automatically populate the dropdown with the values set in the previous step. Review the options in the <strong>Values</strong> tab.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-13-form-update.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-13-form-update.png\" alt=\"Form Update with Job Level Field\" class=\"img-fluid\"></a></div>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"mt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">4</span> Continue by creating an automation rule that activates when the demo request form is submitted and the prospect\'s Job Level is either <strong>C-level</strong> or <strong>Vice President</strong>. Set the action to <strong>Adjust prospect score</strong> by 15 points.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-13-automation-rule.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-13-automation-rule.png\" alt=\"Automation Rule Setup\" class=\"img-fluid\"></a></div>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"mt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">5</span> Before publishing the automation rule, preview it to ensure that it matches only the intended prospects. Remember, the automation rule is retroactive and will apply to all prospects who have previously filled out the form.</p>\r\n\r\n[guide id=\"403\" status=\"closed\"]\r\n'),
