(852, 415, '_solution', '<p>Dynamic Content in Account Engagement is a great way to customize your landing pages. It can also be used to manage static elements on your page that change on a yearly basis, such as year or company information in landing page footers. In today\'s challenge, dynamic content is used to display a relevant message to decision makers in an organization and capture their attention.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5>Step-by-step Guide</h5>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">1</span> For today\'s task, start by creating dynamic content to add to the landing page. Use the <strong>Job Level</strong> field created in the previous challenge. The dynamic content will vary based on the prospect\'s job level. For <strong>Vice President</strong> or <strong>C-Suite</strong> levels, display an alternative title: <em>Lead and Innovate with AI Insights</em>. Include default content as well.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-14-edit-dynamic-content.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-14-edit-dynamic-content.png\" alt=\"Editing Dynamic Content\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\r\n\r\n[guide id=\"381\" status=\"closed\"]\r\n\r\n<p class=\"mt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">2</span> Next, navigate to the landing page you wish to edit and go to the <strong>Landing Page Content</strong> tab in the editor. In the landing page editor tab, select the main-title section and insert the dynamic content you created in Step 1.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-14-add-dynamic-content.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-14-add-dynamic-content.png\" alt=\"Adding Dynamic Content to Landing Page\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"mt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">3</span> Save your changes and preview the landing page to ensure the dynamic content displays correctly.</p>\r\n'),
