(938, 444, '_solution', '<p>You have successfully promoted a valuable piece of content and managed the score of engaged prospects. This initiative serves multiple purposes - it helps promote content, identifies interested prospects, and measures their level of interest. By using this approach, you can increase engagement and gain valuable insights into the preferences and interests of your prospects.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5>Step-by-step Guide</h5>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">1</span> The first step in this challenge is to import the new layout template. Then, create a new form and publish a landing page based on the imported layout template.</p>\r\n\r\n[guide id=\"93\" status=\"closed\"]\r\n\r\n<p class=\"mt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">2</span> Do you know that you can upload your marketing files to Account Engagement and see how prospects interact with them? Today, you will upload a research paper (in .pdf format) to Account Engagement and set a completion action for it. When a prospect views the PDF file, the score will go up by 5 points.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-16-comp-action.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-16-comp-action.png\" alt=\"Completion Action Setup\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"mt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">3</span> There are two ways to provide the PDF file to a potential customer. Option 1 is to send an automated email with the link to the PDF file. Option 2 is to include the link in the confirmation message after the customer fills out the form. In both cases, remember to include a link to the asset from Account Engagement. Otherwise, the completion action will not be triggered.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n'),
