(969, 451, '_solution', '<p>By using Progressive Profiling, you\'ve not only gathered more valuable information about your prospects but also improved their experience by reducing form fatigue.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5>Step-by-step Guide</h5>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">1</span> Before enabling progressive profiling on the form, you should create a new field in your instance that will be included on the form. When creating the new field, ensure that you enable the option for <strong>Recording and displaying multiple responses</strong>. This feature allows you to record a response each time a prospect submits the form without losing previous entries. You can name the field as <strong>Challenge</strong>, and you have the flexibility to change the field label on the form.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-17-create-a-field.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-17-create-a-field.png\" alt=\"Creating a New Field\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\r\n\r\n[guide id=\"114\" status=\"closed\"]\r\n\r\n<p class=\"mt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">2</span> Next, locate the form where you want to enable progressive profiling. Click on the Progressive tab and select the <strong>Company</strong> field. You can also choose multiple fields to display the <strong>Challenge</strong> field only if the prospect already has data in those field(s).</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-17-prog-profile.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-17-prog-profile.png\" alt=\"Progressive Profiling Setup\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\r\n\r\n[guide id=\"95\" status=\"closed\"]\r\n\r\n<p class=\"mt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">3</span> Optional: To enhance the user interface (UI) of the form, you might want to consider changing the field label for the <strong>Challenge</strong> field. You can update the label to <strong>What data analysis barriers does your organization face?</strong>. After making this change, proceed to publish the form. If you are testing the form for the first time, please remember to revisit the page, as the new field will only be visible upon your second visit.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-17-form-field.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-17-form-field.png\" alt=\"Form Field UI Enhancement\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\r\n'),
