(992, 455, '_solution', '<p>Did you know that you can increment the value of a field in a completion action every time a prospect engages with your content? This feature allows you to track a significant metric. Check out the guide below to learn how to enable it for your forms.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5>Step-by-step Guide</h5>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">1</span> The first step is to create a new custom field in your instance. Set the field type to <strong>Number</strong> so that its value can be incremented. If you only update the field value from Account Engagement, you need to modify the field sync behavior.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-18-custom-field-org.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-18-custom-field-org.png\" alt=\"Creating a New Custom Field\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\r\n\r\n[guide id=\"114\" status=\"closed\"]\r\n\r\n<p class=\"mt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">2</span> In the second step, you will utilize the field in the completion action. Navigate to the Completion Actions section and select <strong>Increment prospect field value</strong> from the Action menu. Choose the field you wish to increment and specify the desired amount for the increase. In this challenge, the increase is set to 1, but you can select any incremental value.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-18-view-pdf.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-18-view-pdf.png\" alt=\"Setting Up Completion Action\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\r\n\r\n[guide id=\"121\" status=\"closed\"]\r\n\r\n<p class=\"mt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">3</span> That\'s it! With the <strong>Increment prospect field value</strong> action, you can track the average number of resources downloaded by each prospect and make adjustments to your campaigns accordingly.</p>\r\n'),
