(1230, 514, '__links', 'field_64dd1a2199239'),
(1231, 514, '_solution', '<p>Opting out doesn\'t have to be a permanent farewell. By redesigning the unsubscribe page to align with NextData\'s branding and values, and by providing a straightforward way to resubscribe, you can create a positive final interaction, keeping the possibility of future engagements open.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5>Step-by-step Guide</h5>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">1</span> The visuals of both the unsubscribe and preference center pages are managed through layout templates. It is important to have a unique layout template for each of these pages. To begin, update the layout template that you imported from the resources section.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-25-unsusbcribe.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-25-unsusbcribe.png\" alt=\"Updating Layout Template\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\r\n\r\n[guide id=\"93\" status=\"closed\"]\r\n\r\n<p class=\"mt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">2</span> To complete today\'s challenge, there is one more setting you need to configure. Under the \"Unsubscribe Prompt Page\" section, check the <strong>Use two-click unsubscribe</strong> checkbox. This will open additional fields that you need to fill out. You can add a friendly message here and recommend prospects to update their preferences instead of unsubscribing completely.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-25-two-click.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-25-two-click.png\" alt=\"Two-Click Unsubscribe Setting\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"mt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">3</span> Make sure to test the unsubscribe process to ensure a smooth user experience for your prospects.</p>\r\n'),
