(1373, 545, '_solution', '<p>Sending timely renewal reminders is an important step in keeping customers. It helps to maintain a strong relationship with your customers and increases the chances of them renewing their subscriptions or contracts with your business. By setting up a strong process, you make sure that these reminders are sent out consistently and quickly. This not only reminds customers about their upcoming renewals but also shows your dedication to providing great customer service.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5>Step-by-step Guide</h5>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">1</span> For this challenge, you will use an Engagement Studio program. If you haven\'t noticed already, the Engagement Studio program helps fulfill many operational needs. The first step in this solution would be to create a new dynamic list that captures prospects whose contact will expire in the next thirty days. The criteria for the dynamic list would be that the contact renewal date is equal to or less than 30 days in the future.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-30-dynamic-list.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-30-dynamic-list.png\" alt=\"Dynamic List for Contract Renewal\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\r\n\r\n[guide id=\"120\" status=\"closed\"]\r\n\r\n<p class=\"mt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">2</span> Next, prepare all three templates. You will send one email when a prospect becomes eligible, one email 15 days before a customer\'s contract renewal date, and one email 1 day prior to the renewal date.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-30-templates.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-30-templates.png\" alt=\"Email Templates for Contract Renewal\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"mt-3\"><span class=\"badge text-bg-secondary\">3</span> Let\'s put all the components together and create the Engagement Studio program. There are a few points you need to consider:\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li>Email Schedule: The email should be sent out every day of the week.</li>\r\n        <li>Eligibility: Prospects can be eligible for this program an unlimited number of times, as long as the contract renewal date is within the last 30 days.</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    For the program steps, follow these instructions:\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li>Send the initial email as soon as a prospect becomes eligible.</li>\r\n        <li>Add two rule nodes before sending the next two emails: Day 15 and Day 1.</li>\r\n        <li>At any point, if the contract renewal date is changed to a future date, the subscriber list will no longer be eligible for the dynamic list and will exit the Engagement Studio program.</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-30-esp.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/day-30-esp.png\" alt=\"Engagement Studio Program for Contract Renewal\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>'),
