(1628, 663, '_description', '<p class=\"mb-0\">NextMobile has just launched a new \"Gigabit Fibe 1.5\" Internet package. The marketing team is eager to notify all users who haven\'t yet upgraded to this new package. Your task is to identify these users.</p>'),
(1629, 663, '__description', 'field_64dd19ca99237'),
(1630, 663, '_detail', 'For today\'s challenge, you will use the <code>WHERE</code> clause with a comparison operator to filter the rows you retrieve from a given dataset. Your task is to find everyone who <strong>is not</strong> subscribed to the Gigabit Fibe 1.5 package.'),
(1631, 663, '__detail', 'field_64e26bc8efb7b'),
(1632, 663, '_resources', '<p>The dataset provided contains information about the user\'s internet subscription package. There are two options available:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Update the existing data extension by adding a new column (internet_package) and importing the dataset.</li>\r\n	<li>Create a new data extension from scratch with columns for id and internet_package.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"fs-5 my-4 text-success\">Dataset</h3>\r\n\r\n<!-- Table start -->\r\n<div class=\"table-responsive\">\r\n  <table class=\"table table-striped\">\r\n    <thead>\r\n      <tr>\r\n        <th scope=\"col\">id</th>\r\n        <th scope=\"col\">internet_package</th>\r\n      </tr>\r\n    </thead>\r\n    <tbody>\r\n      <tr>\r\n        <td>003500M7Q93CKG2je2</td>\r\n        <td>Fibe 500</td>\r\n      </tr>\r\n      <tr>\r\n        <td>003500339Kgli7N5t9</td>\r\n        <td>Fibe 500</td>\r\n      </tr>\r\n      <tr>\r\n        <td>003500oS7XRqSuGyQ2</td>\r\n        <td>Gigabit Fibe 1.5</td>\r\n      </tr>\r\n      <tr>\r\n        <td>0035003Xgg2dDhmjRB</td>\r\n        <td>Fibe 500</td>\r\n      </tr>\r\n      <tr>\r\n        <td>003500Sr76b5k8V6n7</td>\r\n        <td>Gigabit Fibe 1</td>\r\n      </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n  </table>\r\n</div>\r\n<!-- Table end -->\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://github.com/sabuhiy/mc30/blob/main/sql30/sql30_02_NextMobile%20Packages.csv\" class=\"btn btn-success rounded-pill text-white\" target=\"_blank\">üíæ Download</a>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"fs-6 my-4\">Dataset Details: <code>NextMobile Packages</code></h3>\r\n<!-- Table start -->\r\n<div class=\"table-responsive\">\r\n<table class=\"table border-success\">\r\n  <thead>\r\n    <tr>\r\n      <th scope=\"col\">Name</th>\r\n      <th scope=\"col\">Data Type</th>\r\n      <th scope=\"col\">Length</th>\r\n      <th scope=\"col\">Primary Key</th>\r\n      <th scope=\"col\">Nullable</th>\r\n    </tr>\r\n  </thead>\r\n  <tbody class=\"table-group-divider border-success\">\r\n    <tr>\r\n      <th scope=\"row\">id</th>\r\n      <td>Text</td>\r\n      <td>50</td>\r\n      <td>Yes</td>\r\n      <td></td>    \r\n    </tr>\r\n    <tr>\r\n      <th scope=\"row\">internet_package</th>\r\n      <td>Text</td>\r\n      <td>50</td>\r\n      <td></td>\r\n      <td>FALSE</td>    \r\n    </tr>  \r\n  </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n<!-- Table end -->\r\n\r\n<p class=\"mt-5 small\">Update: <strong>2024-02-09</strong> The dataset details have been updated to indicate that the INTERNET_PACKAGE column cannot have a NULL value. The dataset has also been updated.</p>'),
