(1713, 668, '_solution', '<p>Welcome back! Today\'s challenge focuses on customer engagement on the community website. You will use the <code>AND</code> and <code>WHERE</code> clauses to identify inactive members who have the potential to re-engage.</p>\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n<code class=\"language-sql\">\r\nSELECT \r\n    id\r\nFROM [NextMobile Community]\r\nWHERE \r\n    is_active = 1 AND \r\n    logged_12_months = 0\r\n</code>\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n<h5 class=\"mt-4\">SQL Queries and Operators Used</h5>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><code>SELECT</code>: Designate the columns to display.</li>\r\n    <li><code>FROM</code>: Identify the table containing your data.</li>\r\n    <li><code>WHERE</code>: Apply conditions to filter for active profiles.</li>\r\n    <li><code>AND</code>: Displays a record if all the conditions are TRUE.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<aside class=\"bg-light-subtle p-4 my-3 rounded-3 border border-light-subtle\" role=\"alert\">\r\n    ‚ö° Query Result: <strong>215</strong>\r\n</aside>\r\n\r\n<p>Fantastic job! Your query today has helped identify members whom we can encourage to become active participants again in the community website. Each step you take in SQL30 brings you closer to mastering data-driven strategies. Get ready for more challenging tasks ahead!</p>\r\n'),
