(2065, 706, '_solution', '<p>Welcome to Day 18! NextMobile is proactively addressing customer concerns by reviewing orders delayed beyond one week. The SQL query below is crafted to filter out such cases, allowing us to take swift action in remedying any service shortcomings.</p>\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n<code class=\"language-sql\">\r\nSELECT \r\n    order_id, \r\n    date AS order_date, \r\n    ship_date\r\nFROM [NextMobile Orders_2023]\r\nWHERE \r\n    DATEDIFF(day, date, ship_date) > 7\r\n    AND status = \'shipped\'\r\n</code>\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n<h5 class=\"mt-4\">SQL Queries and Functions Used</h5>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><code>SELECT</code>: Retrieves specified columns, here focusing on the order ID, order date, and ship date.</li>\r\n    <li><code>FROM</code>: Points to the table containing the relevant order information.</li>\r\n    <li><code>DATEDIFF(day, date, ship_date) &gt; 7</code>: Uses the <code>DATEDIFF</code> function to find the difference in days between the order date and the ship date, identifying orders with delays of more than a week.</li>\r\n    <li><code>WHERE</code>: Filters the query results to include only shipped orders with significant delays.</li>\r\n    <li><code>AND</code>: Combines multiple conditions in the <code>WHERE</code> clause to narrow down the search.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<aside class=\"bg-light-subtle p-4 my-3 rounded-3 border border-light-subtle\" role=\"alert\">\r\n    üí° <strong>Query Result:</strong> 460\r\n</aside>\r\n\r\n<p>You\'ve used these functions to find a list of late orders that need fixing. This work is critical for NextMobile\'s plan to speed up deliveries and make customers happier. Keep doing this great work to help our operations with data!</p>\r\n'),
