(2145, 710, '_solution', '<p>Welcome to Day 22! Today, you will explore SQL\'s power to manage and analyze data from various sources. The task for NextMobile\'s NPS survey involves compiling a targeted customer list, which demonstrates SQL\'s practical application. Using the <code>JOIN</code> clause, you\'ll merge data from two tables: <strong>NextMobile Users</strong> and <strong>NextMobile Orders</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n<code class=\"language-sql\">\r\nSELECT \r\n    DISTINCT u.id, \r\n    u.first_name, \r\n    u.last_name, \r\n    u.email\r\nFROM [NextMobile Users] u\r\nJOIN [NextMobile Orders] o ON u.id = o.customer_id\r\nWHERE o.date BETWEEN DATEADD(day, -60, GETDATE()) AND DATEADD(day, -15, GETDATE())\r\nAND o.status = \'shipped\'\r\n</code>\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n<h5 class=\"mt-4\">SQL Queries and Functions Used</h5>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><code>SELECT</code>: Begins the process of choosing specific columns for the output.</li>\r\n    <li><code>DISTINCT</code>: Removes duplicate entries from the results.</li>\r\n    <li><code>FROM [NextMobile Users] u</code>: Specifies the dataset containing user information, with \'u\' as an alias.</li>\r\n    <li><code>JOIN [NextMobile Orders] o</code>: Joins user data with order details, using \'o\' as an alias for the orders dataset.</li>\r\n    <li><code>ON u.id = o.customer_id</code>: Links user records to order records based on matching customer IDs.</li>\r\n    <li><code>WHERE</code>, <code>BETWEEN</code>, <code>DATEADD</code>, <code>GETDATE()</code>, and <code>AND</code>: These functions and keywords filter results based on specific conditions, select data within a specific range, modify dates, retrieve the current system date, and combine multiple conditions.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<aside class=\"bg-light-subtle p-4 my-3 rounded-3 border border-light-subtle\" role=\"alert\">\r\n    üí° <strong>Query Result:</strong> 97 rows (as of 2024-02-26)\r\n</aside>\r\n\r\n<p>You\'ve now tackled a vital aspect of SQL queries involving multiple tables. Stay tuned for more challenges that will expand your data manipulation skills.</p>\r\n'),
