(2158, 711, '_detail', 'In today\'s challenge, you\'ll focus on <code>LEFT JOIN</code>, also known as <code>LEFT OUTER JOIN</code>. This versatile SQL clause allows us to merge data from multiple tables. It ensures all entries from the \'left\' table are included, even if there\'s no matching entry in the \'right\' table. This is especially useful when handling optional or incomplete data sets, like survey responses.'),
