(2278, 718, '_solution', '<p>Marketing Cloud\'s Data Views are system-generated tables filled with valuable data on opens, clicks, and unsubscribes, to name a few. The unsubscribe data can offer considerable insights into your audience\'s preferences. This data can help identify patterns or problems leading to unsubscribes. Let\'s examine the SQL query to understand unsubscribe trends and reveal insights that can prompt action.</p>\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n<code class=\"language-sql\">\r\nSELECT \r\n    DATENAME(WEEKDAY, eventdate) AS day_of_week, \r\n    COUNT(DISTINCT subscriberkey) AS unique_unsubscribes\r\nFROM \r\n    [NextMobile Unsubscribe]\r\nWHERE isunique = 1\r\nGROUP BY\r\n    DATENAME(WEEKDAY, eventdate)\r\n</code>\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n<h5 class=\"mt-4\">SQL Queries and Functions Used</h5>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><code>SELECT</code>: Extracts the day of the week from the <code>eventdate</code> and the count of unique unsubscribes.</li>\r\n    <li><code>FROM</code>: Specifies that we\'re working with the <code>[NextMobile Unsubscribe]</code> data view.</li>\r\n    <li><code>WHERE</code>: Ensures we only analyze unsubscribe events where <code>isunique = 1</code>.</li>\r\n    <li><code>GROUP BY</code>: Groups the results by the day of the week, allowing us to track trends across days.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<aside class=\"bg-light-subtle p-4 my-3 rounded-3 border border-light-subtle\" role=\"alert\">\r\nüí° <strong>Query Result</strong>\r\n\r\n<table class=\"table mt-3\">\r\n  <thead>\r\n    <tr>\r\n      <th>day_of_week</th>\r\n      <th>unique_unsubscribes</th>\r\n    </tr>\r\n  </thead>\r\n  <tbody>\r\n    <tr>\r\n      <td>Saturday</td>\r\n      <td>125</td>\r\n    </tr>\r\n    <tr>\r\n      <td>Wednesday</td>\r\n      <td>117</td>\r\n    </tr>\r\n    <tr>\r\n      <td>Monday</td>\r\n      <td>147</td>\r\n    </tr>\r\n    <tr>\r\n      <td>Sunday</td>\r\n      <td>114</td>\r\n    </tr>\r\n    <tr>\r\n      <td>Friday</td>\r\n      <td>125</td>\r\n    </tr>\r\n    <tr>\r\n      <td>Thursday</td>\r\n      <td>146</td>\r\n    </tr>\r\n    <tr>\r\n      <td>Tuesday</td>\r\n      <td>136</td>\r\n    </tr>\r\n  </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</aside>\r\n\r\n<p>By analyzing the output of this query, you might uncover a pattern. For instance, you could discover that unsubscribes peak on Mondays or tend to be lower on weekends. These insights can inform the marketing team\'s email strategy. Perhaps they can experiment with sending emails on days with fewer unsubscribes or try adjusting the content to be more relevant on days with higher unsubscribe rates.</p>\r\n'),
