(194, 1, '2023-11-14 00:04:23', '2023-11-14 00:04:23', '<strong>Step 1: Navigate to Layout Templates</strong>\n<ul>\n  <li>In your Account Engagement dashboard, go to Content > Layout Templates.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/layout-template-1.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/layout-template-1.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\n\n<strong>Step 2: Add New Layout Template</strong>\n<ul>\n  <li>Click the \'+Add Layout Template\' button.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/layout-template-2.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/layout-template-2.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\n\n<strong>Step 3: Name Your Template</strong>\n<ul>\n  <li>Please provide a name for your layout template, for example, \"Event Template\". Additionally, add a tag to help you identify and organize your templates internally.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/layout-template-3.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/layout-template-3.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\n\n<strong>Step 4: Define the Layout</strong>\n<ul>\n  <li>Go to the Layout tab and copy and paste your custom HTML and CSS styling here.</li>\n  <li>Make sure your template includes the following variable tags:</li>\n  <ul>\n    <li>The <strong>%%title%%</strong> is displayed in the browser window.</li>\n    <li>The <strong>%%description%%</strong> is a meta-description that is only visible to search engines. It provides information about your landing page.</li>\n    <li>The <strong>%%content%%</strong> refers to the designated area for the form.</li>\n  </ul>\n  <li>If you have a custom CSS to format your forms, ensure that the checkbox for \"Include default CSS stylesheet (recommended)\" is unchecked.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"border rounded-3 p-2 mb-3\"><a data-fslightbox href=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/create-layout-3.png\"><img src=\"https://marketingcloud30.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/create-layout-3.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"img-fluid\"/></a></div>\n\n<strong>Step 5: Save Your Layout Template</strong>\n<ul>\n  <li>After completing all updates and previewing your layout template, click on <strong>Save</strong>.</li>\n</ul>\n', 'How to create a layout template', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '93-autosave-v1', '', '', '2023-11-14 00:04:23', '2023-11-14 00:04:23', '', 93, 'https://marketingcloud30.com/?p=194', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
